  <description>Plants in loose tufts, green to yellow-brown.  Stems 1–5(–8) cm.  Leaves folded and sometimes crisped when dry, flexuose when moist, ovate-lanceolate, gradually narrowed from ovate base, sometimes coarsely serrated above, 2.5–5 mm, keeled distally, not sheathing at base, margins revolute from base to leaf middle; costa stout, mostly percurrent; laminal cells mostly 2-stratose; distal laminal cells mostly subquadrate; basal laminal cells elongate, shorter at the margins, rectangular, incrassate, alar cells enlarged and pellucid.  Seta (7–)10–20(–22) mm.  Capsule yellow-brown, slightly furrowed when dry, 1.5–2 mm.  Spores 18–25 µm.</description>
  <phenology>Capsules mature late spring–early summer.</phenology>
